4. ``three men and a baby,'' buena vista, $83,925,233, no nominations
5. ``untouchables,'' paramount, $76,254,308, 4 nominations
6. ``secret of my success,'' universal, $66,987,694, no nominations
7. ``stakeout,'' buena vista, $65,374,551, no nominations
8. ``lethal weapon,'' warner bros., $65,192,350, 1 nomination
9. ``witches of eastwick,'' warner bros., $63,749,955, 2 nominations
10. ``dragnet,'' universal, $57,201,679, no nominations
in a bid to reduce vandalism, the city is offering small rewards for help in catching people who deface or damage public property
for one year beginning next month, the city will give $120 rewards to people who help police catch vandals, according to finnish newspapers and english-language ``wanted'' posters seen in downtown helsinki this week
we chose english for the posters because `wanted' is such a well-known word,'' city spokesman pertti mustonen told the associated press. finland has two official languages, finnish and swedish
mustonen said the defacement or destruction of telephone booths, public transportation vehicles and other city property costs $950,000 a year
j.c. ``pete'' sebastian, who served the likes of winston churchill and cary grant at his store outside the gates of hearst's castle in the 1930s and 1940s, has died at the age of 81
sebastian died wednesday at twin cities hospital of a heart attack, said his daughter, mary sebastian hansen of boca raton, fla
in addition to running the store bearing his name, he served the tiny, rolling hills community of san simeon as its postmaster, notary public and registrar of voters
the general store, which included gas pumps, a coffee shop and post office, is registered as a state historical monument, ms. hansen said
sebastian worked as a landscaper around san francisco publisher william randolph hearst's art-bedecked mansion in the 1920s. now a museum run by the state department of parks and recreation, the sprawling home is one of the most popular tourist attractions in california
hearst, founder of the newspaper chain that carries his name and model for orson welles' classic movie ``citizen kane,'' often entertained celebrities and business and government notables at the hilltop mansion
churchill, grant and playwright george bernard shaw were among the many prominent visitors to the store sebastian took over from his father in 1933. he sold the shop in 1971 and retired, said bob buddell, the store's present owner
sebastian told an interviewer in 1986 that he always considered the hearsts neighbors, dating back to the pre-castle days when they stayed in the hotel bayview next to his family's store
here is a list of foreigners believed held by kidnappers in lebanon, with the dates they were reported seized:

american
