the market rallied last week and monday as some of investors' worst fears about the business outlook eased
but expectations for economic growth and corporate profits remain subdued, and many market participants are evidently reluctant to buy stocks with the dow hovering around the 2,000 level
speculation has also died down lately that the federal reserve will take any new steps in the immediate future to relax its credit policy
