a spokesman for royale belge declined to disclose the terms of the sale
societe generale, belgium's largest holding company, is the target of a hostile takeover bid by italian financier carlo de benedetti
de benedetti claims he controls 38 percent of societe generale's 28.2 million shares outstanding and has launched a bid for another 15 percent
