british petroleum co. plc said its fourth-quarter earnings rose by 95 percent, under the accounting standard used by most u.s. oil companies, with profits bolstered by stronger gains in refined products, chemicals and minerals
the world oil giant, which acquired full ownership of cleveland-based standard oil co. last year, said it earned 394 million pounds, or $683 million, compared with 202 million pounds, or $281 million, in the fourth quarter of 1986
earnings per share totaled 81.6 pence, compared with 44 pence a year earlier. earnings per american depositary receipt, each of which equals four shares, were $1.42, vs. 61 cents in the fourth quarter of 1986
sales totaled 6.8 billion pounds, or $12 billion, in the october-through-december period vs. 6.6 billion pounds, or $9.4 billion, in the 1986 fourth quarter, the london-based company said
for the full year, the company said it earned 1.3 billion pounds, or $2.1 billion, compared with 1.8 billion pounds, or $2.6 billion
earnings per share totaled 208.8 pence, compared with 388.4 pence in 1986. earnings per american depositary receipt totaled $4.61 last year, compared with $5.72 in 1986, when the dollar was stronger
revenue for all of 1987 totaled 27.6 billion pounds, or $45.2 billion, up from 27.2 billion pounds, or $39.9 billion, in 1986
the figures are based on the ``replacement cost'' system of accounting, which is most directly comparable to the last-in-first-out system used by virtually all major u.s. oil companies
under this method, the value of inventories is listed according to their market value at the time they are used and must be replaced
by tradition, however, bp also uses the ``historical cost'' method of accounting, under which inventories are valued at their original cost on a first-in-first-out basis
in its report issued thursday, bp said that under the historical cost method, its profit rose 10.2 percent, to 260 million pounds, or $471 million, in the fourth quarter, from 236 million pounds, or $341 million in the last quarter of 1986
the results included a loss of 134 million pounds, or $212 million, on the value of inventories over that period
for the year, the company said it earned 1.4 billion pounds, or $2.3 billion, under the historical cost method, compared with 817 million pounds, or $1.2 billion in 1986
earnings per share totaled 298.8 pence in 1987, vs. 178.4 pence in 1986. earnings per adr totaled $4.61, compared with $5.72
despite a substantial fall in the dollar against sterling and softening of oil prices in the last quarter, our results for 1987 represent a robust performance in a difficult year,'' said bp chairman sir peter walters
the stock market turned downward near the close of a quiet session today as traders apparently shied away from the 2,000 level in the dow jones industrial average
analysts said there was little in the economic news to prompt traders to take big positions either way
