international business machines corp. researchers have made the world's fastest dynamic memory computer chips, the company said wednesday at a research conference in san francisco
the experimental chips can retrieve a bit of information in 20 billionths of a second, three times as fast as the current generation of so-called d-ram chips
d-ram chips are the most common kind of memory chips in computers. they are more compact and cheaper but also slower than static random access memory chips, known as s-rams
separately, ibm said it had built an experimental s-ram chip that can retrieve information in a record 11 billionths of a second. it announced another experimental s-ram capable of storing 1 million bits of information, unprecedented for that kind of chip
the announcements were made at the annual international solid-state circuits conference, an event that draws top researchers from the united states, europe and japan
a meat industry group has asked the government to investigate whether south korea has violated international trade practices through its 3-year-old ban on imports of u.s. beef
the american meat institute said it filed a complaint tuesday with the office of the u.s. trade representative, contending south korea's import ban is ``unjustifiable, unreasonable and burden or restrict united states commerce.'' the ami said the import ban is actionable under section 301 of the trade act of 1974
manly molpus, president of ami, said that historically the united states was the major supplier of high-quality beef to south korea, a market that averaged about $5 million a year
molpus said south korea was in violation of obligations under the general agreement on tariffs and trade and under tariff concessions agreed to in the tokyo round of multilateral trade negotiations. year</head>
the venezuelan government foresees trouble in making foreign loan payments this year but a top government official denied wednesday the country will seek new terms for repaying $20 billion in refinanced debt
we will make every effort this year to prevent a significant drop in international reserves, but this will depend on oil prices,'' finance minister hector hurtado told a press conference
we think we can partially cover the oil price drop,'' hurtado said
petroleos de venezuela president juan chacin guzman said recently the state oil company will earn around $15 per barrel on its oil exports in the first half of the year, or $1.70 less than the company's $16.70 per barrel estimate for the year
the drop means around $1 billion less in oil income, according to private estimates
the oil company originally estimated oil earnings this year of $9.6 billion, while other exports could reach $1.3 billion
hurtado said the government would be paying around $3.5 billion this year in interest and principal on its $32 billion foreign debt. it will amortize $400 million of refinanced debt
renegotiations (on the refinanced debt) make no sense while we continue to pay interest,'' hurtado said
he said the drop in oil income will be partially covered by $300 million more from exports of aluminum and gold
the government will also press for multilateral loans and foreign direct investment, and it is considering additional issues of dollar-denominated bonds, he said
last week the government launched a $100 million eurobond issue aimed at venezuelan investors
the government recently reduced the private sector import budget to around $7.2 billion but indicated there could be further cuts
the central bank's foreign reserves were $9.3 billion at year-end 1987, including $3.5 billion of operating reserves
the nation is in technical default of its refinancing agreement if operative reserves fall below $2 billion
a bailout plan in the $1.4 billion collapse of real estate syndicator equity programs investment corp. is expected to continue despite the financial problems of epic's major mortgage insurer, officials said wednesday
however, the decision last month by tmic insurance corp. to halt claims payments put into default 6,600 of epic's properties with unpaid balances of $485 million. deeds to those properties were offered to lenders in lieu of foreclosure, said john cross of skyline financial services corp
that means the lender assumes ownership, rather than the partnerships that had been formed by epic to buy the properties
virginia-based skyline has been hired to oversee the sale of epic's properties. the number already had been reduced to 12,500 from 20,000 in the past two years before the tmic default
cross said the epic bailout was expected to proceed despite tmic's difficulties
meanwhile, state insurance commissioner roxani gillespie said talks are under way between her agency, the federal national mortgage association (fannie mae) and private mortgage companies in efforts to rescue tmic and the epic bailout plan
a new actuarial study indicating how deep tmic's troubles are is expected to be completed later this month, ms. gillespie said wednesday
fannie mae, a major purchaser of mortgages from epic, was the lead agency in arranging the epic bailout plan
tmic is a subsidiary of the nation's leading title insurer, ticor, and has been operating under state conservatorship since april 1986
the bulk of tmic's problems stemmed from the collapse of epic
tmic had insured about 45 percent of the 20,000 mortgages worth $1.4 billion syndicated by epic as tax shelters for the well-heeled. in 1985, epic defaulted on the mortgages and the insurers were left holding the bag
besides tmic, two other major mortgage insurers had large liabilities when epic collapsed: mgic investment corp., a unit of milwaukee-based northwestern mutual life insurance co., and republic mortgage insurace, a unit of chicago-based old republic international corp
officials of mgic and republic said their companies were continuing payments under the epic plan
epic, which was based in falls church, va., was the real-estate investment arm of community savings &amp; loan association of bethesda, md. in 1986, community sought chapter 11 protection from creditors and subsequently was acquired by mellon bank of pittsburgh, pa
the stock market gave ground in late trading thursday as traders apparently shied away from the 2,000 level in the dow jones industrial average
dow jones's average of 30 blue chips dropped 14.58 to 1,986.41 after closing slightly above 2,000 in the week's first two sessions
declines outnumbered advances by about 7 to 6 among new york stock exchange-listed issues, with 688 up, 813 down and 478 unchanged
