increased farmer selling of soybeans also pressured futures prices, but the losses were limited by news of new soybean oil sales to india and expectations for more export business, said richard loewy, an analyst in new york for prudential-bache securities inc
based on the profit-taking which could have ensued, you're still looking at good underlying strength'' in the soybean market, loewy said
corn prices followed soybeans lower, while wheat prices retreated on expectations of adequate near-term supplies, he said
